ğŸ”¹ Problem: Valid Anagram (Easy)
ğŸ”¹ Approach Used: Sorting, HashMap

ğŸ’¡ Problem Explanation:
Given two strings s and t, return true if t is an anagram of s, and false otherwise.
An anagram is a word formed by rearranging the letters of another word, using all the original letters exactly once.

ğŸ“ Solution 1: Sorting Approach (O(n log n))

#include <iostream>
#include <algorithm>
using namespace std;

bool isAnagram(string s, string t) {
    if (s.length() != t.length()) return false;
    sort(s.begin(), s.end());
    sort(t.begin(), t.end());
    return s == t;
}

int main() {
    cout << isAnagram("anagram", "nagaram") << endl; // Output: True
    cout << isAnagram("rat", "car") << endl;         // Output: False
    return 0;
}
âœ… Sorting both strings and comparing them
âœ… Time Complexity: O(n log n)
âœ… Space Complexity: O(1)
